Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Chop the @potato{1} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel!). Pop the wedges on a large #baking tray{} in a single layer. Drizzle with @oil{} and season with @salt{¼} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat, sprinkle with @nigella seeds{½}, then spread out and roast on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{25-30%mins}. Turn halfway through cooking.

> Use two baking trays if necessary - you want the potatoes nicely spread out.

== Yoghurt Sauce ==

Roughly chop the @coriander{1}(stalks and all) and mix with @Greek style natural yoghurt{150%g} in a bowl. Season with salt and pepper and pop to one side for later.

== Bhaji Patties ==

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}). Zest and halve the @lime{1}. Trim the @carrot{2}, (no need to peel). Coarsely grate the @paneer{½} and half the carrots (you'll need the remaining half of the carrots for the salad later on).

> Keep the paneer nicely chilled in the fridge until you are ready to use it for easy grating!

Pop the grated carrot and paneer in a large #bowl{}. Add the @North Indian style spice mix{1}, @cornflour{20%g}, garlic, lime zest and half the @mango chutney{2}. Season with salt and pepper. Using your hands, mix well to combine and shape into patties (pressing the mixture tightly together as you do this) about 2cm thick and roughly the width of your burger buns, 1 patty per person.

== Cooking Bhajis ==

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot, carefully place your bhaji patties in the pan, cook for ~{5-6%mins} each side.

> You may need to fry in batches so you don't overcrowd the pan.

Once fried, transfer the bhajis to a baking tray and pop them into the middle shelf of the oven for ~{6-8%mins} to firm up. Meanwhile, halve the @seeded burger bun{1}, then pop them onto the tray with the bhajis for the final ~{2-3%mins} to warm through.

== Carrot Ribbon Salad ==

Meanwhile, trim the root from the @baby gem lettuce{1} then separate one leaf per person and pop to one side. Thinly slice the remaining baby gem widthways for your side salad. Take the remaining carrot(s) and use a #vegetable peeler{} to peel long ribbons from all sides of the length of the carrot. Stop when you get to the carrot centre. Mix the carrot ribbons and sliced lettuce together in a bowl with a squeeze of lime, drizzle of @olive oil{} and season with salt and pepper.

== Assembly ==

Spread a layer of mango chutney on the base of your burger buns. Add your bhaji and lettuce leaf. Drizzle on some of the yoghurt sauce and serve any remaining alongside for dipping the wedges. Pop the bun lid on top gently. Serve with a portion of wedges and salad. Enjoy!